k Chair Chairs Advisor";s:3:"alt";s:14:"chairs advisor";s:3:"url";s:92:"https://www.chairsadvisor.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/How-to-Fix-a-Sinking-Desk-Chair.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQpPh9M0iClmMYEzzxPcgnCWlpP-1NTAiL_5g";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:500;s:6:"height";i:788;s:6:"source";s:62:"https://www.chairsadvisor.com/how-to-fix-a-sinking-desk-chair/";s:6:"domain";s:21:"www.chairsadvisor.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:73:{i:0;s:22:"Buy Links affiliateIN.";i:1;s:88:"This video shows a tutorial on how to fix a sinking office chair for less than a dollar.";i:2;s:34:"See more of my content and follow.";i:3;s:27:"Use a Hose Clamp Duct Tape.";i:4;s:52:"Cheap Fix Temporary Not Adjustable Not Professional.";i:5;s:87:"One of the more common DIY quick fix or hack is to use a hose clamp and some duct tape.";i:6;s:103:"This option does not actually repair the office chair but can stop your chair from temporarily sinking.";i:7;s:71:"Essentially there are 3 ways to fix your chair that keeps sinking down.";i:8;s:78:"Option 1 Change the Pneumatic Cylinder already described above Option 2 Fix a.";i:9;s:110:"If your desk chair keeps on sinking whenever you sit or get off the chair it could happen due to many reasons.";i:10;s:69:"It would help if you found them so that you can know how to fix them.";i:11;s:48:"The common could be a loosely adjusted cylinder.";i:12;s:52:"For this you need to change it to a suitable height.";i:13;s:49:"For this purpose trace the lever under the chair.";i:14;s:171:"You can fix a sinking chair by replacing the gas cylinder using a Chair Saver Kit a Plastic spacer or PVC pipe or a hose clamp or a jubilee clip and duct tape combination.";i:15;s:28:"All these are DIY solutions.";i:16;s:110:"Before you think of throwing out that office chair one of these solutions are bound to restore its proper use.";i:17;s:48:"Your sinking office chair will now stop sinking.";i:18;s:74:"You may need to add or remove the length of the pipe to adjust the height.";i:19;s:61:"WikiHow has a good tutorial for the repairs to office chairs.";i:20;s:26:"PVC pipes and hose clamps.";i:21;s:102:"Slide the plastic tube from the extendable cylinder so that you can see the metal cylinder underneath.";i:22;s:25:"Clean the metal cylinder.";i:23;s:56:"Another quick and easy fix is using the chair saver kit.";i:24;s:97:"It has spacers that snap on over the cylinder and wont slide down the shaft like a jubilee clamp.";i:25;s:50:"No tools or chair disassembly required to install.";i:26;s:50:"And it can be used again if something else breaks.";i:27;s:147:"The technique you use to fix a sinking chair depends on your budget your level of expertise the flexibility required and the permanence of the fix.";i:28;s:128:"Methods like hose clamp and PVC are cheap and dont require too many skills while replacing the cylinder requires a professional.";i:29;s:95:"The next step will be to drill a small whole right where the shaft meets the base of the chair.";i:30;s:60:"Ensure that you use a drill with the same size as the screw.";i:31;s:74:"Lastly you will insert a screw into the hole and then tighten it properly.";i:32;s:72:"Once you do it well the chair will not sink at all no matter the weight.";i:33;s:117:"Another quick and easy fix for a sinking office chair instead of replacing the cylinder is using the chair saver kit.";i:34;s:97:"It has spacers that snap on over the cylinder and wont slide down the shaft like a jubilee clamp.";i:35;s:63:"Get a hose clamp or a jubilee clip to wrap around the cylinder.";i:36;s:83:"The usual size of a hose clamp to repair an office chair is around two centimeters.";i:37;s:74:"To apply the hose clamp loosen its screw and slowly pull out the belt end.";i:38;s:74:"Wrap the clamp around the metal cylinder but do not tighten the clamp yet.";i:39;s:136:"If you want a permanent solution about how to fix the sinking office chair you will need to replace the pneumatic cylinder o